    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. I've heard some people arguing that those \"mixed-income\" requirements and other regulations actually just make it harder to build and drive up costs more. It seems like the biggest obstacle to affordable housing is actually just people fighting against these density projects. Do you think the main thing holding back progress is just opposition from people who want to keep their neighborhoods exactly as they are?",
