      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "NIMBYism, or \"Not In My Backyard\" opposition, is undeniably a major obstacle to necessary urban progress. Resistance from entrenched residents who prioritize maintaining low-density, car-dependent suburbs actively stalls the creation of affordable, vibrant urban cores. These opponents often fear change and prioritize preserving outdated neighborhood aesthetics over the collective need for sustainable housing and infrastructure. Ultimately, the political will to overcome this resistance is what determines the pace of smart city development.",
      "source": "target",
